product_title: Amazon eGift Card - Hoops and Yoyo Cake Face (Animated) [Hallmark]
review_headline: Fast, but not without its flaws.
review_body:
These giftcards are great for multiple reasons:

You want to get something expensive, but don't have the money on any one card.
You want to send someone an instant gift card to their email to shop with
You simply don't like the physical variation

For people who don't have high limits on any cards, or have enough money in their checking account this is an especially convenient choice.

As Amazon doesn't allow you to pay with multiple cards, you would instead use your respective cards to buy yourself one of these gift cars. You redeem them to your account. Rinse and repeat.

This makes it so you can buy that one expensive item you normally could not afford on any one of your cards.

DOWNSIDE:

While the first 2 or 3 of these will be fairly instant (within 5 minutes) you will run into a wall if you try to buy to many at once. After about 3 in a short period of time Amazon will be forced to manually authorize each of these with their respective banks.

This can take 3-4 hours.

product_title: Amazon Gift Card - Print - Happy Birthday (Presents)
review_body: Needed a quick gift due to a last minute invitation, and this was clearly the best solution. Sure, I could give cash or check, but I knew the birthday boy wanted a few things from Amazon that were well over the typical gifting amount. I hate giving gift cards, but with the amount and variety on Amazon, I actually prefer receiving them over having to deposit cash or checks.

Amazon makes gift card giving so simple. The old days, people spend so much time and $ picking out a card, and write some good words on the card. There must be some people who wished that they could erase and made changes to words on the card. After that, the card looked like scrap and got tossed. Another card was purchased and the process started all over again. When completed, actual gift (a check, cash) was then placed in the envelope to be delivered to that special someone. $5-10 was spent on top of the gift. I am avoiding all that hassle by sending Amazon gift card.

I like the gift card option for kindle because I hate the fact you can only purchase one item at time for kindle. No one wants to put multiple single items on their credit or debit cards. So I by a gift card for myself and then redeem and buy all my kindle items that way. I would love to be able to skip the step of having to email it to myself and then redeem it. Why don't you guys offer an instant gift card for your kindle accounts. By and redeem at the same time. That would be perfect! Otherwise its a great way to buy kindle items.

product_title: Amazon.com Gift Cards - Print at Home
review_body: Amazon Gift Cards are a great gift for a lot of different occasions. Since most people use Amazon for something, and you can use the gift cards on almost everything, they are useful for a lot of people. It's extremely easy to buy a gift card. You get a few different ways to deliver your gift including printing a physical card and emailing it to the recipient. The reason I only gave them 4 stars is that when emailing a gift card you can specify the date you would like it to be delivered, but you cannot specify the time on that day. This made me have to print the gift card instead of emailing it because I didn't want it delivered too early. Printing the gift card was extremely easy and makes a decent looking card. Overall these are a great gift choice.

4. Scratch off the adhesive on the back off the gift cards and enter the code
5. You're all set! You can choose whether to use your gift card balance during the payment section of checkout.

review_headline: Easy to buy -- easy to use
review_body: I like this gift card for several reasons. Amazon has something for everyone, which makes it a good solution for the people who have everything or for the people whose tastes are different from my own. For instance, I don't know what books or music to buy for my grandson. It's best that he be able to chose for himself. I like being able to buy the card online and to print it on my printer and not having to wait for it to arrive in the mail. Using the gift card is easy for the recipient as well. Everyone I know has access to a computer. Also there is no surcharge for using the card. In contrast, I received a Visa gift card last year. To use it I had to go to a retail store because it had to be activated at a register -- I couldn't use it online. In addition, it had a $4.95 activation fee.
Great to buy what you or someone else wants!
